#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:205
msgid "Rationale and alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:208
msgid "Keep scoped threads in external crates."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:210
msgid "There are several advantages to having them in the standard library:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:212
msgid ""
"This is a very common and useful utility and is great for learning, testing, "
"and exploratory programming. Every person learning Rust will at some point "
"encounter interaction of borrowing and threads. There's a very important "
"lesson to be taught that threads _can_ in fact borrow local variables, but "
"the standard library doesn't reflect this."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:217
msgid ""
"Some might argue we should discourage using threads altogether and point "
"people to executors like Rayon and Tokio instead. But still, the fact that "
"`thread::spawn()` requires `F: 'static` and there's no way around it feels "
"like a missing piece in the standard library."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:222
msgid ""
"Implementing scoped threads is very tricky to get right so it's good to have "
"a reliable solution provided by the standard library."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:225
msgid ""
"There are many examples in the official documentation and books that could "
"be simplified by scoped threads."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:228
msgid ""
"Scoped threads are typically a better default than `thread::spawn()` because "
"they make sure spawned threads are joined and don't get accidentally "
"\"leaked\". This is sometimes a problem in unit tests, where \"dangling\" "
"threads can accumulate if unit tests spawn threads and forget to join them."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:233
msgid ""
"Users keep asking for scoped threads on IRC and forums all the time. Having "
"them as a \"blessed\" pattern in `std::thread` would be beneficial to "
"everyone."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:237
msgid "Return a `Result` from `scope` with all the captured panics."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:239
msgid ""
"This quickly gets complicated, as multiple threads might have panicked. "
"Returning a `Vec` or other collection of panics isn't always the most useful "
"interface, and often unnecessary. Explicitly using `.join()` on the "
"`ScopedJoinHandle`s to handle panics is the most flexible and efficient way "
"to handle panics, if the user wants to handle them."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:245
msgid "Don't pass a `&Scope` argument to the threads."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:247
msgid ""
"`scope.spawn(|| ..)` rather than `scope.spawn(|scope| ..)` would require the "
"`move` keyword (`scope.spawn(move || ..)`) if you want to use the scope "
"inside that closure, which gets unergonomic."
msgstr ""

