#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:254
msgid ""
"Crossbeam has had [scoped threads](https://docs.rs/crossbeam/0.7.1/crossbeam/"
"thread/index.html) since Rust 1.0."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:258
msgid ""
"There are two designs Crossbeam's scoped threads went through. The old one "
"is from the time `thread::scoped()` got removed and we wanted a sound "
"alternative for the Rust 1.0 era. The new one is from the last year's big "
"revamp:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:262
msgid "Old: https://docs.rs/crossbeam/0.2.12/crossbeam/fn.scope.html"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:263
msgid "New: https://docs.rs/crossbeam/0.7.1/crossbeam/fn.scope.html"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:265
msgid "There are several differences between old and new scoped threads:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:267
msgid ""
"`scope()` now propagates unhandled panics from child threads. In the old "
"design, panics were silently ignored. Users can still handle panics by "
"manually working with `ScopedJoinHandle`s."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:271
msgid ""
"The closure passed to `Scope::spawn()` now takes a `&Scope<'env>` argument "
"that allows one to spawn nested threads, which was not possible with the old "
"design. Rayon similarly passes a reference to child tasks."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:275
msgid ""
"We removed `Scope::defer()` because it is not really useful, had bugs, and "
"had non-obvious behavior."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:278
msgid ""
"`ScopedJoinHandle` got parametrized over `'scope` in order to prevent it "
"from escaping the scope."
msgstr ""

#: src/3151-scoped-threads.md:281
msgid ""
"Rayon also has [scopes](https://docs.rs/rayon/1.0.3/rayon/struct.Scope."
"html), but they work on a different abstraction level - Rayon spawns tasks "
"rather than threads. Its API is the same as the one proposed in this RFC."
msgstr ""

